From a665d40515db3ab7b02f47dc12d71069dfcf9771 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 09:50:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf: optimize notification/status polling to reduce Vercel
 traffic

- Add usePageVisibility hook to detect background tabs
- admin/layout.tsx: 30s -> 60s interval, skip fetch when tab hidden,
  refetch immediately when tab becomes visible again
- dashboard/layout.tsx: same treatment for associate notif count poll
- dashboard/page.tsx: remove aggressive 30s background timer,
  30s -> 90s interval, skip when hidden, refetch on visibility return
- status/page.tsx: 30s -> 120s interval, skip when hidden, refetch
  on visibility return

Root cause: 4 separate setInterval polling loops (one of them
duplicated on the associate dashboard) fired unconditionally every
30s regardless of tab visibility, causing sustained ~200k+/day
invocation volume on Vercel starting right after the notification
feature rollout.
